Package: sondage
Type: Package
Title: Survey Sampling Algorithms
Version: 0.1.9999
Authors@R: person(given = "Ahmadou",
                  family = "Dicko",
	          email = "mail@ahmadoudicko.com",
		  comment = c(ORCID ="0000-0002-9654-7582"),
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fast implementations of survey sampling algorithms for drawing
    samples from finite populations. Provides equal probability methods
    (simple random sampling, systematic, Bernoulli) and unequal probability
    methods (Brewer, conditional Poisson/maximum entropy, systematic PPS, Pareto piPS,
    Chromy's sequential PPS, Sequential Poisson, Poisson, multinomial).
    All sampling functions return design objects carrying sample indices,
    inclusion probabilities, and design metadata. Generics compute joint inclusion
    probabilities, pairwise expectations, and sampling covariances for variance estimation.
    Based on algorithms from Tille (2006, <doi:10.1007/0-387-34240-0>)
    and the generalized framework of Chromy (2009).
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
